<HEADLINE>
FT  08 MAY 91 / World News in Brief: Rubens recovered
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Rubens' painting Aurora, stolen from a Spanish museum six years ago, was
recovered in Florida. An undercover US customs agent arrested four Miami
residents who tried to sell him the painting for Dollars 3.5m (Pounds 2m).
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
<PAGE>
London Page 1
</PAGE>
